UNRESTRICTED I(1) ESTIMATES:
	X_t  = A_1 X_{t-1} + ... + A_k X_{t-k} + rest + epsilon_t, epsilon_t ~ N(0,Omega),

I(1) ESTIMATES FOR RANK 2:
	Z0_t = Pi Z1_t + Phi Z2_t + rest* + epsilon_t, epsilon_t ~ N(0,Omega),

I(1) ESTIMATES FOR RANK 2:
	Z0_t = Pi Z1_t + Phi Z2_t + rest* + epsilon_t, epsilon_t ~ N(0,Omega),
	Z0_t = DX_t, Z1_t = X_{t-1} | W_t | D^r_{t-1}, Z2_t = differences | D^u_{t-1}.

UNRESTRICTED I(1) ESTIMATES:
	X_t  = A_1 X_{t-1} + ... + A_k X_{t-k} + rest + epsilon_t, epsilon_t ~ N(0,Omega),

---------------------------- CATS( 2): I(1) VECM
The dataset is:              
The estimation sample is:    6 - 891
The dependent variables are: R_95_ETANOL_HIDRATADO R_95_OLEO_DIESEL R_95_GASOLINA_COMUM star_ETANOL_HIDRATADO star_OLEO_DIESEL star_GASOLINA_COMUM
Unrestricted variables:      Constant
Deterministic specification: Unrestricted Constant (H_lc, CATS::DRIFT)


I(1) ESTIMATES FOR RANK 3:
	Z0_t = Pi Z1_t + Phi Z2_t + rest* + epsilon_t, epsilon_t ~ N(0,Omega),
	Z0_t = DX_t, Z1_t = X_{t-1} | W_t | D^r_{t-1}, Z2_t = differences | D^u_{t-1}.
